comments: ['75% of the time when I open the app a screen to "grab my offer" will pop up with no option to close it. I\'ll scroll back and forth without seeing any way to close this screen, and the only way to avoid this has been to close and reopen the app then press the back button at exactly the right time to stop it from opening. This isn\'t a practical or reliable method needless to say. The popup offers have greatly reduced the quality of the app for me.', "Initially it was really handy to have this family with pets setting and be able to record the dates of flea treatments etc for to know when they were due. The minute I signed up it wouldn't let me use the app unless I chose out of two different plans designed for a grooming business for invoicing. I can't seem to get back to the family with pets option and now all my info has been lost. This issue needs to be sorted for those who aren't using this for business purposes.", "5/2023 Updated Review: You had something that worked perfectly for my needs and then you went and messed with it! Added annoying ads for a setting, pop up notifications for social media that I don't need or want, and things flashing red for some reason. Old review 5 stars: great app really helps me keep track of the dogs care. Med reminder is better than some human ones I often put myself in as a pet for the Med reminder.", "Making it not able to use an old version that was working is quite awful on your part. I hate this updated version, I can't even scroll to see all of my animals (I have around 100), I have to search them to see the ones that are on the bottom of the list. My only option is to hide my dead animals, I can't still see them on the bottom of the page. Please make the old, not updated version able to be used again.", "We have been using the app for 2 years. All of a sudden we are asked to pay €50 excluding tax for accessing our data and continue using the app. I admit that the app is covering our needs but considering we don't live in the US or EU, annual €50 fee is not an affordable amount for the most of the customers living out of US or EU. You should consider arranging suitable fees accordingly for different countries. Edit: The lifetime subscription offer was fair enough. Thank you 11pets.", "The best application to keep a medical control of your pet, I have used several applications of this type and by far this is the best of all, it's so easy to use and it is the most complete, you can keep a comprehensive record of what happens to your pet, which other apps are limited to keeping track of the basics. Other points in favour of this application is that you have the option to add different pets and not only dogs and cats, like ferrets or guinea pigs.", 'I have loved this app for years. I use it to keep my service dog\'s info available whenever I need it. Now you are forcing us to pay for a subscription, even though on your website it still states "join now for free forever." First, that is false advertising, second, many of use have relied on your app for years. Why are you charging us so much, especially since you are still advertising that is is free? And why not offer monthly as well as yearly? There are a lot of people that cannot afford it.', 'Revising my review yet again, sticking with 1 star since the app is now constantly spamming the email I gave them with DOZENS of emails at this point, asking for a €55 fee, repeating again and again how the "free version will expire soon" but never giving a definite date, a situation that has been going on for around a year now. Sad to see what used to be a handy app turn into this mess and instead of owning up to their mistakes the devs handling this all so unprofessionally.', 'I paid for No ADs but your app pops up Offering Special fee every time I opened the app. What the hell I paid for??', 'Before I put in any info, I could look at everything the app had to offer, it was full of interesting things and places I could go to keep track of my pets info. Once I put in mine and my pets info, I could NOT get the app to do ANYTHING, but try and get me to join more things. I scrolled all the way down to the bottom, thinking, there has to be a button somewhere to get back to my account, but nothing. I tried the 3 bars at top right, the image, the arrow, but nothing. 👎👎👎👎😖😡', "The app is amazing - so helpful for my fur family of 2 dogs and 2 cats. Especially for the senior cat who requires medication every other day, the notifications are great. And keeping track of the senior dog that tends to have tummy trouble a lot. So helpful to have information available to give the vet. But also, the 11 Pets Support Team is awesome. I recently had a problem with synchronizing my information on a new phone. Multiple attempts failed, even when things remained fine on my old phone. Anyway, the Support Team was very responsive and communicative. They quickly looked into the matter, and it's been resolved. An awesome app with fantastic support!", "Overall it's good except for one thing. It would be really nice for people with many pets if you can record n select multiple pets at once. It is really inconvenient to go into each of their profiles individually and key in one by one when i have 10 pets with the exact same info/vetVisits. Hope to be able to see some changes for this on the next updates.", "Not always super intuitive, but otherwise a great app for keeping track of your pet's needs. I really like that I can track everything - from medical conditions, food supplies and periodical care, to small stuff like cleaning. In the beginning it's a bit strange - especially the food supplies section is somewhat difficult to get the hang of, but once you get used to it, it's great and super helpful.", "Excellent app, for most of the stuff (some European vaccines were missing), and certainly offering more detailed options unlike the others I have tried. But, I knocked two stars off for the subscription-based payments (damn Adobe that has started the fad! 🤦🏽\u200d♀️), and for quite an expensive app on a yearly basis. With all the costs included in having a pet I just can't afford to pay that price, no matter how much I want to support the developers.", "I'll be moving away from this app with the new €55 one-time payment. It's too expensive for what it does. The UI of the app is cluttered, unattractive and unintuitive. That said, there are probably more features than any other app out there, IF you actually need them. I want to track weight, vet visits, vaccinations and grooming schedule in a simple user interface. For €55, this isn't it.", 'Although a little difficult to navigate and find data, it’s quite comprehensive. I would rate it 4/5, but poor business practices from developers steered me into a poor rating. If an app is offered as shareware, and you disclose its price beforehand, I’d have no problem with it. This app was offered as freeware a couple of years ago; and now that we’ve input lots of data, they changed it to being a paid app. I’ve already started migrating all my data.', "This app is very close to being useful, if it added just a bit more customization. I have 1 cat and 2 lizards, and the reptiles need very different scheduled care than a mammal. If I could add a relevant icon to the custom reminders (like cleaning their enclosures), or have a way to record things like when they shed or the # of urates/feces found in a week, it would be really great! As is, it's just not useful to me.", "i liked it at first.. it's good in that you are able to customize it in pretty much any way you can think of but navigating and editing schedules is so frustrating. I had 3 pets on it and made a vaccine schedule for each of them put the wrong date on one and even when it says its deleted. it still kept popping up when i went back to the main schedule page. Way easier just to use my phone calendar.", 'Subscription of 50 Euros per year is insanely expensive. I hope your team would consider a free version with limited features. I don\'t think I need most of the new features from your future update... I wouldn\'t mind ad popping up once in a while and may even consider subscribing if the price is reasonable and affordable. Plus, is there a way to export the data? I don\'t want to lose my cat\'s data but I am not certain I can afford your "small subscription fee".', "I can track meds, supplements, grooming, and appointments easily. There is a place for labs, contacts, conditions, and even a food inventory that tells you when you are about to run out! I can track feedings but not calories. If there was a food data base for meals and a way to attach my cat's fitness tracker to this app it would be perfect.", "Out of all the pet tracking apps out there, I find this one the best! I've been using it with my dog for her entire life. I just wish the Supplies tab was more general instead of geared towards just food. I would love to be able to track her monthly preventatives. Right now, it only lets you choose per meal or per day for the tracking. Also, I wish the Vaccines showed the group name instead. For example, my dog gets the Lepto4, which is 4 lepto vaccines. I made a group, but when I choose it, the list shows all 4 vaccines (which can be confusing). Overall the app is great. Buttons are in odd places and it takes some getting used to, but after using it a few times you remember where they all are. And I LOVE that it syncs with my iPad and that I can use their web portal too.", 'Really helps with reminders! I love having all the info in one place and can answer any questions the vet has or know when I need to get supplies! I do wish that there was an option to turn off reminders for medications. When exporting information for the vet, not all of the info is accurate and I wish we could choose the content it provides as well as be able to print it out! If we could do the upgraded content in a one time purchase, instead of monthly, I would probably do that as well.', "€55 is crazy. It's just a fancy calendar reminder with notes. You lose all your precious data anyway if the app collapses like many do. Then they often sell your data. I'll just revert to keeping Notes plus calender reminders on my phone like I used to. Or perhaps a Google sheet. It works exactly the same, and without all the spam I've been getting from 11pets lately, trying to get money for the same service they initially gave for free.", 'Is a great place to get your pets life under control. Meal measurements, growth, worming due date, how much food you have left and when you need to get more, this app almost has everything. Edit: I take back the thing about extra notifications. Turns out the notification setting I thought turned off all the notifications (including the ones I needed) only turns off the social media ones. So this app works great for me. Have not tried info transfer or appointments though.', 'So far a good app, although I have a feature request: My birds weigh around 60-70 grams, but the weight graph shows 0 - 1 kg. It is impossible to see a trend on that scale. But zooming in, also zooms in the dates. So I would like the app to automatically zoom the y-axis to the normal range (with some margin). In my example the y-axis could scale to 50-90 grams, while the x-axis should still be zoomable.', "I've been using the app for over a year. It wasn't great, but it was the best available – I gave up on keeping track of how much food I have left because it never seemed to work right, I had trouble finding and setting up features – notification setting are in like 3 different places. There have been bugs and some annoying issues here and there. It's definitely not something I'd pay 50 Euros annually for, so I'll be looking for a replacement. It's not a small fee to me and not worth it.", "This app gives you a lot of ways to keep track of your pet's health. Customizable screens, lists, and reminders make it easy to keep track of just the information you care about. You can also attach pictures and documents to records, although I do not use this functionality yet. The medication and care reminders are the features I use most, and I am starting to keep track of vet visits and incidents as well. Support is very responsive, if you run into any issues. My only complaint is that there is no matching web portal, so I can only see the tracked information in the app. I would love to be able to use my PC's web browser to view and add information.", "Becoming paid is unattractive. I've been using this app for a very long time and it has been excellent. I use this app to track my pets weight and give me reminders for medications and vaccinations. There should be a free version for these basic functions. I have no problems with you offering an upgrade to those wanting extended features. But for simple things like I mentioned, I will not be paying €55. This is a shame", "This app has pretty much everything I was looking for in maintaining all of my animals healthcare. As others have mentioned, it would nice to be able to edit or change the animal's medicine or vaccinations without having to delete or snooze. Also, even after deleting the information, it continues to show up in the reminder.", 'Even though I can\'t really afford it, I took advantage of the limited time "lifetime subscription" offer. I can\'t lose years worth of records for my sanctuary, and having a monthly or annual subscription fee would be beyond unaffordable. I haven\'t found another app as well designed and thought out as 11 Pets, that could take its place. The app itself I would give 5 stars. Putting me between a rock and a hard place earns a 1. I rated it based on the average.', "I looooove this App! I have over 30 reptiles/amphibians and this app allows me to keep track of feeding, weight, birthdays and reproduction. I have to customize a few things, but its so easy to do and simple to manipulate. Everyone is shocked when I show them the app, that I can keep track of them so well. Great app! And I don't have to deal with annoying pop-ups or ads. Thanks for a universally awesome app!!!", "I've used this app for years, but I mainly use it to keep track of my pet's weights, especially those with medical conditions that require their weight to be monitored, and note incidents (track my dog's occasional seizure). Now that the free version is going away, I can't justify paying €69 a year to use two of its features. I'm not opposed to paying a yearly subscription, but that fee is more than I pay for subscriptions on apps I use on a daily basis.", 'This app is a great idea, but could be really improved with some additional measurements. Would really like to track the cats outputs as well as inputs to ensure she is healthy and see what impact her diet and supplements are having on her digestive health. Also some way to track water consumption would be great. This may already possible, but when there are more than one care giver it would be useful for both to see and make entries to the pets profile using the app on different devices..', "I have been using this app for several years for my dog's information and it has been perfect for incidents, measurements, and reminders for treatment. Recently, I logged in with a new phone and my dog's weight history appeared to have been converted to a different unit of measure and the history was off. I emailed support and they got back to me almost immediately and fixed it right away. None of my data was lost and I wanted to share that this app and their customer service are top notch! 👌", "Can't adjust the portion size of meals without having to reenter every meal making it be marked twice in the schedule, also the schedule section would greatly benefit from being more organized and easier to read. I really like the app but it is so frustrating to have to constantly redo everything whenever I adjust my cats meals.", "Was a good app but no where near worth the premium price they're forcing, saying you're going to update it doesn't justify the price you're charging.", 'Very helpful for keeping records and etc for about my dog, and removes a lot of anxiety about me possibly forgetting or losing something important. I especially really love the gallery feature-- if you guys ever add an option to uplaod multiple images at a time save images from the gallery, and/or download an entire gallery I would be ecstatic but other than that. I really love this app for helping me keep things organize and saving my poor phone from hundreds of low-quality chihuahua pictures.', "I really like this app now, especially after the last update. Some colors were added and it looks nice. Maneuvering around the app was a little difficult to figure out at first, but now I'm a master at it. The app is very thorough and excellent with time schedules and record keeping. I also like the fact the app doesn't consume too much battery power, nor does it slow down the phone.There's always room for improvement, but this is a great app to have if you need to keep track of your fur-babies health.", "I like the app so far. Was having five animals it's hard to keep track of everything and this app does make it a little bits easier. I'm still learning my way around it. But I think there could be some improvements to it. You should people have one or two dogs. I have two dogs. But I also have ferrets and people usually have more than one or two ferrets. I think would be great if they can integrate more on that side of things for exotic animals as well as even customize it more.", 'Information is entered in a very "databasey" and challenging manner. The same information can be entered in multiple places, some of the locations can\'t be extracted into any of the "sharing" reports. DO NOT PUT WEIGH INTO APP! Any weight entered is converted into the wrong weight on "shareable" petsitter report. I reported problem and of course the fix is always an update away. (After 2 updates ii give up) I emailed customer service multiple times with no response. Poor experience all around!']

title: Tamadog - Puppy Pet Dog Games
description:
Have you ever dreamed about having a dog? About a cute little puppy that you will take care of… Dreams come true with dog life simulator Tamadog. It is your new virtual pet. Care for it, love and make it happy.

Your new virtual friend 🐩

Don’t hesitate and get a dog right now. Such a lovely, charming and cute puppy, who likes having fun, eating yummies and taking selfies. You’ll never get bored with it. Discover the Tamadog’s bright world with a variety of exciting adventures in dog town.

Meet your new virtual friend in the Tamagotchi dog game. Just look at these cute eyes that will melt your heart… Play talking puppy games, give it delicious treats, take it for walks and just have fun all day long. Pet dog games are made for love. Give your doggy all your love and it will definitely love you back.  

Check out the Tamadog pet simulator and enjoy taking care of your little faithful friend. Imagine that you are playing dog sim Tamagotchi - now the gameplay is in the real pet world… It's a dream come true.

TAMADOG COOL FEATURES:

🐶 VIRTUAL PET IN YOUR REAL HOME. Don't forget to give your pet care everyday. Feed it, clean and play with it. You can play both 3D and AR games mode. Allow the app to use a phone camera and your puppy will appear right inside your house. 
🐕 RAISE A SMART PET. Record voice commands and train your dog. From “sit down” to “break dance” – you can teach your dog lots of cool tricks. Talk to your friend. You doggy is so sociable and eager to learn. That is my dog - you will say proudly. 
📸 CAPTURE AMUSING MOMENTS. Take cute selfies with your puppy and its dog life, make hilarious videos and share them with friends.
🎰 UNLOCK NEW LEVELS. Keep raising a happy pet, play dog games and enjoy extra activities as a reward.
👗 DRESS UP YOUR PUPPY. Stylish suits for agile male pups and fancy dresses for fluffy girl puppies - dress up your little friend trendy.
🥰 ULTIMATE CUTENESS. Your new friend loves you and goes head over heels when you rub its belly. Can you imagine that your doggy will gladly lick your nose anytime you move the screen closer? All possible with animal games. 
🎮 MINI-GAMES. Your puppy is asleep or you just need to relax from the daily routine? Try yourself in exciting mini-games in a dog simulator and set your records. There are a lot of puppy games for free for any taste: shooting bubbles is just as entertaining as healing and grooming your dog in diverse and enjoyable lovely pets mini-games.

The only virtual dog that looks like and feels like a real dog. Feed it, pet it, play with it. Take it wherever you want, your doggy with its pet’s world is always at hand. You’ll never get bored with it.

Show everyone how adorable your puppy is. Try to catch all the bright moments spending together with your virtual friend in puppy games. Take amusing and funny selfies with your AR dog and create your own photo album full of happy memories.

Your pet is tired? Take a break - play mini puppy games free to not feel bored. Challenge yourself in exciting Match 3 games, while your pet is resting. Discover more than 300 levels of the game and try to finish all them to earn special gifts for your talking dog. Play dog games for free and make your pet happier.

TRY PREMIUM ACCESS 
Subscribe for Premium and get unlimited access to all the AR dog game features:
🍖 Unlock all premium items
🍖 Unlock AR mode
🍖 Free daily coins and diamonds

Time has come! Get a puppy with the Tamadog pet games. Love it, care for it and make sure it is becoming your best friend. 💗
summary: Have fun with cute puppy games and raise your charming dog!

comments: ['This game is ok but at the start if you press dont allow acess to photos you cant go back and change it which is really annoying and it also takes ages to grow up and in the adds it looks like you can like have it on your bed and in real life through your phon but that DOES NOT... work for me but otherwise its a good game.', "My 4 year old managed to some how spend £43 on coins even though I have fingerprint approval I emailed for them to take back all the coins and refund and they refused Not a single coin has been spent, the game hasn't even been played She ended up getting it via an advert", "I understand pay to play games but they make it stupid simple for kids to accidentally buy a $15/WEEK package. Per week. As in $60/mo. That's not an oopsie that's exploitation. They know kids are going to do it and that some parents won't dispute the charges so they're making bank. And the ads are incessant, the game is basically unplayable. My daughter was sitting right next to me and I feel like there were ads every 60 seconds.", "This game is not for three year olds C. T damson mazzthats why you had to pay for it I think you are crazy to think that. anyways I love it so much Yes there are some ads but you mash the X an then your all good 👍so yeah I don't care what people think of it I just know that this is a very fun game and they should be grateful that there even is a game LIKE this. You're welcome people that made this game.", "This app should be taken down. My child downloaded, and I was charged 16.09. I don't even know how the purchase went through. Look at all the other reviews! This is happening way too much! Google really needs to do something about this!", "The game is automatically 5 Star's it took me forever to pick one out of three puppies but when I picked one oh Wow! The game is amazing like your cat game the puppies are adorable so thanks for making these games for us to have as pets", "Wish I could give no stars. My daughter accidentally purchased 40 on this when trying to exit out of the ad to purchase some Mexican thing for the dog. I think it's stupid these games do that with the ads instead of having normal ads where u watch a video etc it has ads for purchasing and if u accidentally hit wrong button it automatically charges u. I have requested a refund from game in Google play & as soon my bank opens tomorrow I'm calling have payment canceled and reversed back as well", "I love it a lot very good app I played a lot that's why I give it five stars it's really amazing 🤩 but sometimes there's ads", "I love the game maybe less ads and it's so cool for me cause l just happend to LOVE dogs so keep up the good work people.👍♥️🐶", "I am loving this game Its so amazing! I hope I can see more animals like baby Cat the color ginger and little baby tiger I know it will be awesome if this game can make one it is going to be my favorite game of all!♡ . when I found this game F fell in Love with it: D it was awesome I would say this game is for the people who don't have a dog OR some other type of animal this is a truely lovely game! I will be continue to Play the game and have so muck fun. with it hope you guys get this Letter", "I love this game if you dont want to pay dont pay like it's that simple I love this game it's like you have your own dog just 1 problem too many ads so please fix that and please update it more becuz it just needs more updates but otherwise I love this game and keep up the good work", "Deserves 0 stars. Just refund my money please!!! My 3 year old purchased this silly game by accident and within minutes I requested a cancellation and refund which I was denied. I'm beyond furious, I don't understand how an organization functions like this!!! Very lame game, not even worth the purchase even by choice!", "My son accidentally pressed subscribe and I've been charged three different times Google won't give me a refund and I can't figure out how to end my subscription", 'Just a money grab. WAY too easy to accidentally spend money. My son spent 40$ with just a couple of clicks. Its not even fun. Absolutely Uninstalling this terrible game.', 'The dog is cute but It forces you to Pay a monthly subscription witch is 40$ And the adds TO MANY ADDS!! Also the minigames r soooo boring😑There is literally nothing to do. 😡😡😡😡Btw my sister accidentaly payed and got grounded So THANKS ALOT', "Worse app my cousin accidentally pressed the subscription and spent 4k pesos my mom sent me and that was supposed to be spent to my hospital billing I requested a refund within a minute and was denied the next day this is frustrating and ridiculous don't download this app, SCAM!", "Predatory. This is a children's game. As soon as my daughter downloaded and started it, I got a notification that my card was charged. My daughter said she couldn't play until she pressed a button( it was a subscription button). It's very easy to accidentally subscribe. I looked on Google play and saw this app cost 10 dollars a week. 40 dollars a month for a game. Absolutely not.", "I love this app, its so cuuuute. But what I hate about it is that it keep forcing me to pay it and also, there is so many ads. That thing that pops up is so annoying. How am I suppose to enjoy my game when ya'll keep forcing us to pay😒 And Oh Gosh! The camera thing scares me. 😱 Oh and plus, the game is getting boring. The mini games are so boriiing. I was expecting something fun, but its not. ☹", 'This game is a nice little game for kids it shows responsibility to kids when they get a dog🐶🐶🐶🐶', "I love it Tama dog is so fun too play I'm about to sleep and I remember tamadog is not sleeping yet", 'I love the game great work big thumbs up!', 'This game collect money from kids without permission or even anything you should uninstall it immediately', 'Really good and the fun and the dog🐕 is really cute 😍', 'My daughter loves this game she loves the cute puppy 💕😍 also', "This game is cute you guys are mad and goofy- there's nothing to purchase plus I just want to get the dog into my camera but this game is cute you guys just pay for something😀", 'if theres lower than 1 star option, i will select it.. i just had an unauthorized purchased from this app,Nice phising strategy that as soon as the user download the app for free it will give them subscribe or purchase button that they cannot move forward unless they click it. in my case, a minor accidentally click the button then next thing i know, i got an email notification saying thankyou for your purchase. what a smart way of scamming people.', 'You guys are illegally allowing payments through this game, i HAVE parantel lock on my phone, and NO purchases can be done withput my finger print, so please explain exactly how you deducted from my bank account without my permission and without my supposed secure password or fingerprint!!!! Refund my money and stop robbing people. Dont tell me nonsense, youcannot bypass byometric finger print approval.', "Not so bad in mini games and others but one major issue... The ads, shows dog as VR via using camera, what did I end up, game crash after trying it. I'm not gotta play this game when I can't even meet the ads's main advertisement.", 'Steals you money quick. My 5 year old accidently hit yes to the $32 WEEKLY subscription ad that pops up when your in the app. I tried to get a refund. Was denied.', "It was good but you can't play the mini games for long. You always have to exit and start playing the level all over again", "I can't get past the loding stage and then the 2 other times I did get past it it blocked the screen with premium! You have to restart it 10,000 times! And you have to pay for the VR!", "I was charged $130 over the course of ten weeks for a subscription to this game. Here's the thing, I never installed this app nor approved any such purchase. My daughter said she doesn't know anything about this. Furthermore, I had authentication required on my account. Google refuses to refund my money. This is very unfortunate, as this time of year is the toughest for me financially. My work is seasonal. I wish your company would do the right thing and give me a refund.", "I haven't even played this game yet, it's been installing for hours. I think I'll just cancel instead of installing it looks fun, but like most games the advertisements are usually lies and you can tell them right off the back but this one looks pretty legit so that's why I downloaded it but I guess it was a lie too?", 'Very nice thanks to make this game because I am a dog lovers', 'I have the best puppy ever believed or not I do', "My grandson downloaded this, and I can't afford it. How do I cancel this.", "I don't understand a single thing in the add it said that u can do the thing where it animates it in front of you but it's not showing the opinion to do that. Very bad game", "This game is so cute especially for the people who loves dogs.I love this game but you can see that i rated 3-5 stars and it's because there are too many ads and also you're gonna need to pay! Well maybe if you make it free and less ads, a lot of people would probably install it.", 'I love the game as a dog lover this game is awesome I just wanted some free clothing that\'s it anyways it\'s worth your time download it it\'s really cute and fun try it out (btw if 1 star rewiewers sees this there\'s a "Continue with the limited edition") that\'s all great game!', "I downloaded the app and straight away way asked to subscribe to gain extra rewards but no way of playing without it so I decided to uninstall the app if this changes I would be happy to give the app a second chance but until then I'll leave it alone"]
